
[1]incivility

   INCIVIL'ITY, n. Want of courtesy; rudeness of manners towards others;
   impoliteness.

   1. Any act of rudeness or ill breeding; with a plural. Loud laughter
   and uncomely jests in respectable company, are incivilities and
   indecencies.
